<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-02T22:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-02T22:30:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Entry in the White House Map Room Log <gloss target="#t_Notebook1">Notebook</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <dateline>
                                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-02T23:30:00-04:00">September 2, 1943, 11:30 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                                <p>… President and <gloss target="#t_PM1">P.M.</gloss> in at 2330.
                                    Discussed coming meeting of US.–British &amp; Russia as to place
                                    for it to be held. Talked generally and left at 2350.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>F. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Graham</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>